race.comment: JUSTICE SERVED (2) boasts an unbeaten record at this trip and arrives off a strong effort over two miles when not far away. Earlier in the prep he scored at Grafton in what has since proven a strong form race, and with Zechner back aboard he should get every chance to continue his good run. MARENARO (3) got things back on track last start when closing off strongly into third at Ipswich over 1700m. This is tougher but he's up to the task on the short turnaround. LET FLY (4) disappointed last time but had been consistent prior and her best figures stack up well. Don't underestimate. AUTUNNO (7) good effort to finish second last time carrying 56.5kg over 2000m at Gold Coast Poly. In the mix.
